  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "IT Project Manager (Infra)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Plan and deliver IT infrastructure projects within scope, timeline, and budget.</li><li>Lead technical teams across servers, networks, storage, and cloud platforms.</li><li>Collaborate with stakeholders to define requirements and project deliverables.</li><li>Maintain project plans, schedules, risks, and progress reports.</li><li>Provide technical guidance and ensure solutions meet business and IT standards.</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve complex infrastructure issues.</li><li>Ensure compliance with security policies and industry best practices.</li><li>Manage vendors, procurement, and contracts.</li><li>Mentor and provide technical leadership to team members.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in IT, Computer Science, or related field.</li><li>Proven experience managing or leading IT infrastructure projects.</li><li>Strong knowledge of servers, virtualization, networking, cloud (AWS/Azure), and storage.</li><li>Proficient in project methodologies (Agile/Waterfall) and tools (MS Project, Jira).</li><li>Strong leadership, communication, and stakeholder management skills.</li><li>Excellent analytical and problem-solving abilities.</li><li>Experience in budgeting, risk management, and mitigation.</li><li>PMP, ITIL, or cloud certifications are an advantage.</li></ul><p><br />(EA Reg No: 20C0312)<br />Please email a copy of your detailed resume to <strong>qianyu@talentsis.com.sg </strong>for immediate processing.<br />Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
